        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 2:49PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Butler, moving
northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, half inch hail, and very heavy
rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Peach Grove, Campbell County Lake, Grants Lick, Aspen Grove,
Claryville, Morning View, and Butler.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
